To accurately capture the possibility of pre-existing resistance as well as variability in the tumor volume at the time of diagnosis, for each simulated patient, we sampled clone sizes of each cell type from distributions informed by clinical information5,14,31–36. Thus, each patient had a unique total tumor cell number as well as the frequency of individual sensitive and resistant clones at the start of treatment (Fig. 3b and Supplementary Fig. S9, “Methods” section). Each patient was then subjected to all considered combination schedules, and the efficacy of one schedule relative to another was assessed by estimating the relative improvement. We defined the relative improvement of schedule B compared to schedule A at time \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
